4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO REPORTING ON
5 THE COLLECTION OF STUDENT IMMUNIZATION RECORDS; REQUIRING SCHOOLS TO REPORT
6 ANNUALLY ON IMMUNIZATIONS AND EXEMPTIONS; REQUIRING THE DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC
7 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES TO COMPILE AND REPORT ON COUNTY-LEVEL DATA; AMENDING
8 SECTIONS 20-5-109 AND 20-5-408, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Report of school immunizations and exemptions. (1) A governing
13 authority shall ensure that each school required to obtain student immunization records under 20-5-109 submits
14 an annual report to the department of public health and human services on the immunization records obtained
15 by each school. The report must provide information on the outcomes of immunization record collection efforts
16 required under 20-5-109 and include the following data:
17 (a) the total school enrollment;
18 (b) the number and percentage of students who provide the school with written evidence of having
19 received the immunizations required under 20-5-403;
20 (c) the number and percentage of students who provide the school with a written medical
21 exemption statement for one or more of the required immunizations;
22 (d) the number and percentage of students who provide the school with an affidavit of a religious
23 exemption for one or more of the required immunizations; and
24 (e) the number and percentage of students for whom the school does not have written evidence of
25 immunization as required under 20-5-406 or the affidavit or medical exemption statement required under 20-5-
26 405.
27 (2) Information on the medical and religious exemptions must be broken down to identify the
28 number and percentage of students exempted from each required immunization.
