7 Section 2. Section 20-5-109, MCA, is amended to read:
8 "20-5-109. Nonpublic school requirements for compulsory enrollment exemption. To qualify its
9 students for exemption from compulsory enrollment under 20-5-102, a nonpublic or home school:
10 (1) shall maintain records on pupil attendance and disease immunization and, make the records
11 available to the county superintendent of schools on request, and for nonpublic schools, comply with the
12 requirements of [section 1];
13 (2) shall provide at least the minimum aggregate hours of pupil instruction in accordance with 20-1-
14 301 and 20-1-302;
15 (3) must be housed in a building that complies with applicable local health and safety regulations;
16 (4) shall provide an organized course of study that includes instruction in the subjects required of
17 public schools as a basic instructional program pursuant to 20-7-111; and
18 (5) in the case of home schools, shall notify the county superintendent of schools of the county in
19 which the home school is located in each school fiscal year of the student's attendance at the school."
20
21 Section 3. Section 20-5-408, MCA, is amended to read:
22 "20-5-408. Enforcement. (1) The governing authority of any school other than a postsecondary
23 school shall prohibit from further attendance any pupil allowed to attend conditionally who has failed to obtain
24 the immunizations required by 20-5-403(1) within time periods established by the department until that pupil
25 has been immunized as required by the department or unless that pupil has been exempted under 20-5-405.
26 (2) The governing authority shall conform with the provisions of the Family Educational Rights and
27 Privacy Act of 1974, 20 U.S.C. 1232g, as amended, and its implementing regulations at 34 CFR, part 99.
28 (3) A student's health records, including information related to immunizations received and
